<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br>IMPORTANT!!! NO ORC VETERANS IN THIS DECK< I MEANT MORGUL WARDENS, IMPORTANT!!!!!<br>
<br>
This is the updated version of OF GONDOR AND MORDOR V 1.1<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Strategy, Shadow<br>
<br><br>
This is the officially dubbed; Sauron Army the major goal here is to play no less than two minions at a time, a lesson Ive learned from long hours of my friends Elven archers. Think of your Morgul Hunters as the commanders of your troops, they lead the onslaught of heroes as you land crushing blows to all your opponents cards. <br>
<br><br>
The Pillagers add a nice touch, since taking strength from your opponent is twice as easy as adding it to your minions, very effective agents Dwarf decks. The Tower Assassins are there for their eleven strength and their good game text. Sure you can use Elrond to draw three cards.Need I say more? A very deadly card is the ever-feared Hate, I love it when my opponent plays a Greenleaf or Gorns bow. Well maybe not the bow, but if you throw on a You Bring Great Evil, the lil archer can be devastated. Finaly the MOrgul Wardens go nicely with those cost nine sites, when you can play about five other minions at the same time.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Strategy, Free Peoples<br>
<br><br>
Your starting fellowship will be Boromir: Lord of Gondor, accompanied by Pippin: Mr. Took. What looks like a Super Fellowship Is really no more than a congregation of well chosen speed bumps. Leading the group is Gandalf: The Grey Pilgrim, which not only has high vitality allowing for a nice archery or Isengard Orc sponge, but also has a strength of seven allowing him to survive most skirmishes. As well as that he will draw you a card every turn, now how about that? Ok ill stop acting like a auto salesman- Pippin is always nice to use to play Aragorn or Gandalf for two shadow tokens. Sam is, dare I say it? The speed bump god? Gimli is good to use to beat those minions with killer game text, suck as troop of Uruk-Hai, where anyone else would die or be exhausted, let Gimli take it. On Merry goes the hobbit sword and he becomes a second Gandalf, with a cost of one two.<br>
<br><br>
The Two Gondor companions, Aragorn and Boromir, will do most of this decks work, using a variety of strength damage bonuses, Just be sure to give them their toys and theyll do fine. Also, give the armor to them as fast as you can. If you can only get one, give it to Boromir, because of his game-text he can walk out from the Balrog with two wounds. This deck has a nice healing circle going and I prefer Might of Numinor to Athelas for two reasons. 1) It can heal multiple persons, and 2) its a maneuver event and can be played after you see what youre up against. Last of all, Frying pan goes on Pippin, and Sting on Frodo, wait I think I should be nice and give it to my Morgul Hunterwhat a scary thought.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
After-thought of the cultures.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Dwarven: I usually bring up enough minions to take down at least someone every turn or so, but usually Hate and You Bring Great Evil will do the trick nicely, along with the help of the deadly Orc Pillager. Just watch out for various sponges and Disquiet of Our People, it can be frustrating to have all six of your minions go to a Dwarf Guard.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Elven: I have this down pretty well, thanks to some practice with my friend Skyler. Hate the Legolas as soon as hes wounded, put the You Bring Great Evil on anyone you can, preferably Aragorn, and you should do fine. The high-vitality minions are great agents the archers. Hate and Greenleaf go together like bread and butter.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Gandalf: This Sauron deck you dont need to worry about sleep too much. Although, playing a signet twilight denial deck could suck. And its kinda hard to Hate a wizard with six vitality (Staff and Ring). Simply crush them all with five or six minions and youll do fine.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Gondor: To tell the truth, my Shadow side would completely obliterate my Free Peoples side. Gondors only chance is to get only two minions to deal with at a time, something I hope will never happen. Three and up is the best bet.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Isengard: Orcs? Simple, just shake off all the wounds to your sponges. Since almost all of them have four vitality, its going to be ok. Uruk-Hai? Another story, get some armor, and pray they dont have too many troops. Youll be able to pull through, although you will probably lose your speed bumps rather fast. <br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Moria: Use Aragorns Bow and Greenleaf to pick off the one vits. Then take out the rest with, Gorn Boromir, Gandalf, and Gimli. Even Pippin and his frying pan work good.<br>
<br><br>
If they play a heavy hitting minions deck instead, beat them down with strength bonuses on your main fighters, or sacrifice a sponge, after all, the watcher can be played in two places tops same with the Balrog. Cave troll could be trouble.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Nazgul: As long as they dont play two many at a time, its ok, just ditch the ranger sword and give Aragorn two Flaming Brands. Strength plus six and damage plus two is a small taste of hell to Nazgul. I just envy their Wreathed in Shadow, since all the purposeful archery in this deck is directed, its no problem though.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Sauron: Like I said before, Sauron could be trouble. Just play it through and try and beat them through your shadow side, dont try a rush to site nine because it isnt happening. <br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Hobbit: Let the nasty little boogers have it easy till about site four, then when there stealth is no longer that useful, crush them. Also a good technique is to bluff them out, pretending your not getting any minions, let them accumulate a heavy shadow pile, then let it all out. <br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Sites: Some of these sites are absolutely useless. The first sanctuary mostly, is just there to keep your opponent from doing too much ether. Some are there for a high twilight cost such as the Weatherhills. The only ones that truly help are the Pony and shores of Nen Hithoel. Then maybe Caras Galadhon if they happen to have Proper Poet or Disquiet of out people.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
This is my deck and I hoped you enjoyed it. My E-mail address is silverdrow20@hotmail.com if you have any questions.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Eric Splittgerber<br>
<br><br>
Part of the Rebel Strike Team.<br>
